Reasoning: The paper deals with the spread of epidemics over networks, which is a topic that falls under the subfield of network science. The paper also uses Markov chains and nonlinear mean-field approximations, which are common tools in the study of complex systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Other likely sub-categories include cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems), as these sub-fields are also relevant to the study of complex systems and network dynamics.
